author: News Tribune
title: Lady Jays softball takes district title
text:
Share 
WAYNESVILLE, Mo. — The Jefferson City Lady Jays beat Camdenton 9-6 on Friday to take the Class 4 District 10 championship. 
Hannah Hirschvogel was 3-for-4 with an RBI, Emily Williams was 2-for-3 with two RBI, and Alyssa Schulte doubled twice and drove in two. Taylor Dey added two hits and a run. 
Schulte was the winning pitcher, allowing five earned runs on nine hits and three strikeouts. 
Jefferson City (19-8) plays Wednesday at Blue Springs. ﻿
